<dl id="n09179b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n09" href="#n09179b">N09 (VI.B.1)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n09all.htm#n09179b"> 179(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> basin</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">RIVER ENGINEERING. &hellip; <i>Physical Characteristics of Rivers &hellip; River Basins</i>.- The <b>basin</b> of a river is the expanse of country, bounded by a winding ridge of high ground, over which the rainfall flows down towards the river traversing the lowest part of the valley; whereas the rain falling on the outer slope of the encircling ridge flows away to another river draining an adjacent basin. <small> <a name="EBRV" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#EBRV"><cite title="source">&ldquo;RIVER ENGINEERING&rdquo;Encyclopaedia Britannica</cite></a>, 11th edit. (1911) XXIII 374</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
